comment._content: T&G Building (aka Temperance & General Society Building), 195-203 Elizabeth St, built ca. 1928-1930. Demolished 1975. Also seen here www.flickr.com/photos/51979177@N02/6399415641/in/photostr... ; 1930 SMH item re nla.gov.au/nla.news-article16636417

comment.realname: State Library of New South Wales
comment.author: 29454428@N08
comment._content: A beautiful deco replaced by a 60's modernist, but before all that, the State Library's second great benefactor, Sir William Dixson, had his family tobacco business on this site.
